title: Victory: An Island Tale
creator: Joseph Conrad
description: LibriVox recording of Victory: An Island Tale, by Joseph Conrad. Read by skoval. Recollections of the life of Axel Heyst, one-time manager of the liquidated Tropical Belt Coal Company in a fictitious island in the Pacific. After retreating from society in response to his professional failures, the misanthrope is drawn back by a romantic affair. (Introduction by S. Kovalchik) For further information, including links to M4B audio book, online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.
subject: librivox; audiobook; conrad, literature
